<assessment id="u4_m4_cc3_tutor2">
  <title>Tutor</title>
  <question id="q1">
    <body>What is the chi-square statistic in this case?</body>
    <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
      <choice value="A">494.949</choice>
      <choice value="B"
        >1<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155008-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>000</choice>
      <choice value="C">0.000</choice>
    </multiple_choice>
    <part>
      <response match="A" score="10">
        <feedback>Correct. Indeed, to find the test statistic, we need to add the contributions of
          each of the 4 cells, which in this case is: 62.72 + 115.462 + 111.502 + 205.265 = 494.949
        </feedback>
      </response>
      <response match="B">
        <feedback>Incorrect. It seems like you were adding the observed counts or the expected
          counts (both of which add up to
          1<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155033-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>000)
          instead of the contributions of each of the cells
          <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155044-0500"?>to
          <?oxy_insert_end?>the test
          statistic<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155051-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
          which are the third entry in each cell. </feedback>
      </response>
      <response match="C">
        <feedback>Incorrect. I think you are confused.<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155146-0500"?>
          <?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155144-0500" content="..."?>0.000
          is the
          p-value<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101129T155138-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>
          not the chi-square test statistic. </feedback>
      </response>
    </part>
  </question>
